rmstrong has built a whole metaphysical system, that is, a comprehensive and unified picture of the fundamental structure of the world. The various chapters of the book address the key issues concerning Armstrong' view about the problem of universals, the nature of states of affairs, the ontological ground of possibility, nomic necessity, and dispositions, the truthmaker theory, and the theory of mind. This volume aims to celebrate Armstrong’s memory bringing new understanding, and hopefully stimulating more work, on his philosophy, with the conviction that it constitutes an invaluable heritage for contemporary research in metaphysics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMetaphysics. 0aRealism. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4aNaturalismus. 4aNaturgesetz. 4aTheorie des Geistes. 4aWahrmacher. 4aWissenschaftlicher Realismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aLaws of Nature, Scientific Realism, Naturalism, Theory of Mind, Truthmaker.1 aBorghini, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalemi, Francesco F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalemi, Francesco Federico, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCumpa, Javier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInwagen, Peter van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaurin, Anna-Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellor, D. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Kristie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMumford, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrilia, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 